{
  "comment_text": {
    "dhp384:2": "The commentary says this refers to the mastery of two things, serenity and discernment (cf. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn34/en/sujato#1.3.5'>DN 34:1.3.5</a>). However, the term is not “two” but “duality” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>dvaya</i>), suggesting a link to <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn35.92/en/sujato#2.2'>SN 35.92:2.2</a>, the duality of sense experience. ",
    "dhp416:1": "This verse and the next are identical. The commentary says they were spoken on two separate occasions. "
  },
